### Create and Start Recording with createAsync or Manual Steps

Source: https://github.com/expo/expo/blob/main/docs/public/llms-sdk-v53.0.0.txt

This snippet shows two equivalent ways to create and start an audio recording: using the convenient `Audio.Recording.createAsync` helper or by manually preparing and starting a `Recording` instance. Both methods achieve the same outcome.

```javascript
const { recording, status } = await Audio.Recording.createAsync(
   options,
   onRecordingStatusUpdate,
   progressUpdateIntervalMillis
 );
```

```javascript
const recording = new Audio.Recording();
 await recording.prepareToRecordAsync(options);
 recording.setOnRecordingStatusUpdate(onRecordingStatusUpdate);
 await recording.startAsync();
```

